			<ns0:name>msn...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/105190905030319373792/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Environment variable NACL_CRASH_TEST provides a way for malware to cause all NaCl applications to stop working. If any malicious software is able to insert NACL_CRASH_TEST into the environment that is used when Chrome is started, then all NaCl applications will crash.


&lt;b&gt;What version of the SDK are you using?&lt;/b&gt;
NaCl tip of tree

&lt;b&gt;What version of the runtime are you using?&lt;/b&gt;
NaCl tip of tree

&lt;b&gt;On what operating system?&lt;/b&gt;
Linux

&lt;b&gt;What browser are you using?&lt;/b&gt;
Chrome tip of tree

&lt;b&gt;What steps will reproduce the problem?&lt;/b&gt;
1. Put NACL_CRASH_TEST=1 into the environment (e.g., with &amp;quot;export&amp;quot;)
2. Start Chrome in the same session
3. Navigate to a NaCl application

What is the expected output?
The NaCl application should run.

What do you see instead?
The NaCl application crashes.
